# Archived Summaries

## Phase 9: Discovery Upgrade + Audit Fixes (2026-03-28)
- **Slider-based Aaker derivation:** Replaced fixed personality-pick → scores lookup with soft derivation from 4 sliders (Q7-Q10). Calibration anchors (Nike, McKinsey, etc.) help sanity-check scores. Rationale: rigid lookup produced identical scores for similar inputs; sliders + soft derivation gives more nuanced brand profiles.
- **13-question structure:** Organized into 6 XML categories. Added business context (Q1-Q2), goals/emotion (Q3-Q4), audience (Q5-Q6) that the old 5-question format lacked. These feed directly into Step 2a business signals.
- **Convergence guards expanded to 36 archetypes:** Previous 15 rows only covered website archetypes. Dashboard and app archetypes had no INSTEAD guards, allowing structural convergence. Now all 36 have positive-direction guards.
- **Tailwind build rule:** Made explicit as rule #15 — inline styles only for palette hex. Prevents mockups from drifting to inline-style-heavy implementations.
- **Aligned with /opus:** All new content uses soft language per 4.6 guidelines. No MUST/CRITICAL/NEVER in caps.
## Phase 10: External Website Redesign Mode (2026-03-28)
- **WebFetch-first, Playwright fallback for SPAs:** Static sites use fast WebFetch; SPAs detected by low visible text content (<500 chars) trigger Playwright headless rendering. Keeps simple sites fast while handling JS-rendered pages.
- **Pre-filled discovery from crawl:** Infer Q1, Q2, Q5, Q6, Q12 from crawled content to reduce user effort. Tagged with [inferred] so user can override.
- **Direction D = current site in external mode:** Rather than competitor cluster, D faithfully reproduces the site being redesigned. Gives a direct before/after comparison.
- **Mockup output moved to ~/Projects/Websites/Mockups/ for ALL modes:** Centralizes all design mockups in one browseable location, not buried in .buildrunner/.
- **Logo on all mockups:** Extracted from crawl (external) or project files (local). Favicon as fallback. Makes mockups feel real and branded.
- **Auto-open in browser:** Mockups auto-open after build so user can immediately browse and compare.
