  WHY: Per-project cluster-test-config.yaml templates create silent drift — only BR3 had one; every other project fell through to local testing without sharding. Global default means new projects get distributed testing for free.
  CONTEXT: ~/.buildrunner/config/default-test-config.yaml, ~/.buildrunner/scripts/dispatch-test.sh
  WHY: Explicit overrides win, project opt-ins next, cluster baseline last. Each layer fully replaces the previous (no merge) to keep behavior predictable.
  CONTEXT: dispatch-test.sh lines ~90–155 (config resolution block)
  WHY: Prevents sharding projects that have no tests (would produce spurious "no tests found" failures across the cluster). Detection is grep-based, no dependency resolution needed.
  CONTEXT: dispatch-test.sh — has_vitest/has_pytest detection block
  WHY: dispatch-test.sh's shard semantics (--shard=N/M + vitest reporters) are vitest-specific. Pytest sharding needs pytest-xdist + different flags. Recording pytest as a future extension, not silently breaking it today.
  CONTEXT: dispatch-test.sh pytest branch
  WHY: Simpler than editing YAML to disable. Touch a file = skip dispatch. Works for projects that want local-only testing without authoring a config.
  CONTEXT: dispatch-test.sh opt-out check (early exit before config resolution)
  WHY: Merge semantics on YAML lists (nodes, rsync_exclude) are ambiguous — does project-level rsync_exclude append or replace? Full replacement is explicit; if a project writes a YAML it owns the whole surface. Inheritance can be added later behind an 'extends:' key if needed.
  CONTEXT: dispatch-test.sh config loader, default-test-config.yaml comment
  WHY: Every template copy rots. Cluster changes (add Otis as shard 3, change timeout, add exclude) would require touching N projects. The global default makes every project inherit the change on next run.
  CONTEXT: distributed testing architecture
  WHY: Pre-fix state was "BR3 shards; everyone else runs local and nobody notices." New default flips it: if a project has vitest, shards automatically; deviate via YAML, opt out via marker file.
  CONTEXT: dispatch-test.sh, default-test-config.yaml, future /test + /e2e invocations across ~/Projects/*
